As part of this initiative, please ensure the below serverless best practices are followed across all testing and monitoring activities.

### Best Practices to Follow

* Use filtered/sample datasets wherever possible during validation and testing.
* Apply partition/date filters early to reduce unnecessary scans.
* Fetch only required columns instead of full table reads.
* Reuse cached/intermediate datasets where applicable.
* Prefer incremental validations over full historical reprocessing.
* Review long-running notebooks/queries for optimization opportunities.
* Any notebook, reconciliation, or monitoring script consistently running beyond **10 minutes** should be reviewed for compute optimization opportunities.
* Monitor abnormal execution duration or compute spikes proactively.
* Reuse common frameworks/utilities instead of duplicate notebook logic.
* Schedule heavy executions during appropriate windows where possible.
* Clean up unused temp objects, stale notebooks, and unnecessary intermediate datasets regularly.
* Ensure proper DevOps governance and cost awareness while using serverless resources.

### Practices to Avoid

* Avoid repeated reruns without reviewing root cause/failure analysis.
* Avoid unnecessary historical reloads or full-volume scans.
* Avoid unoptimized joins/cross joins on large datasets.
* Avoid duplicate monitoring logic across multiple notebooks.
* Avoid using production monitoring notebooks for ad-hoc analysis activities.
* Avoid keeping long-running or idle serverless executions active unnecessarily.
* Avoid accepting long-running serverless executions as normal without optimization review.
* Avoid moving notebooks to production without optimization review.

